commit.message: earlyoom.service: redirect stderr and more handening

Update MANPAGE.md

--syslog param added

msg: syslog logging introduced

Useful in embedded applications.

Signed-off-by: Konstantin Menyaev <KAMenyaev@sberdevices.ru>

Let systemd set Nice and OOMScoreAdjust

to avoid warnings on startup (with -p):
 Could not set priority: Permission denied. Continuing anyway
 Could not set oom_score_adj: Permission denied. Continuing anyway

go.mod: update golang.org/x/sys

Closes https://github.com/rfjakob/earlyoom/pull/288
Fixes https://github.com/rfjakob/earlyoom/security/dependabot/1

earlyoom.default: make comment match changed default

Fixes e1c74d918c3951e0ec20bd8817ab55530e020491

Print both "mem total" and "user mem total" on startup

Relates-to: 459d76296d3d0a0b59ee1e2e48ad2271429de916
README: fix typo in link
README: update changelog
README: note that sysrq-trigger problem has been fixed in Linux v5.17

Introduce UserMemTotal and calculate MemAvailablePercent based on it

Shmem/tmpfs may block a large part of RAM. This memory cannot be freed
by killing processes. Before this change, we could get into a
situation where earlyoom kills *every* process, but still cannot
achieve the desired MemAvailablePercent.

Fixes: https://github.com/rfjakob/earlyoom/pull/274
Fixes: https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1012870

Revert "Don't kill anything if there's not enough anon memory used"

The next patch will handle this is a smarter way.

This reverts commit 42860d6cc149868e087c106eb894a5274bf17212.

Fix typos

Found via `typos --format brief`
Adding an option to ignore processes owned by root

README: drop lgtm badges

LGTM will shut down in dec 2022
https://github.blog/2022-08-15-the-next-step-for-lgtm-com-github-code-scanning/
kill: include process_mrelease() in process exit time

kill: open pidfd before kill()

Otherwise process_mrelease() fails in 50% of cases with ESRCH.
Now it works reliably (as least with the "tail /dev/zero" test).

meminfo: drop MiB variants

Feels like the duplication causes more confusion than it helps.
Create codeql.yml

Don't kill anything if there's not enough anon memory used

When /dev/shm and /tmp (when on tmpfs) gets filled up, earlyoom
would start killing everything, without improving the situation.

Check if we *possibly* could kill enough processes (i.e. anon memory)
to get the available memory over the minimum. If not, do nothing.

Fixes: https://github.com/rfjakob/earlyoom/pull/274
Fixes: https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1012870
meminfo: export MemAvailableKiB
make format
meminfo: add anon pages
kill.c: add comments to BADNESS_PREFER/AVOID constants
Makefile: complain if we don't have VERSION

github ci: also run "make test" where golang is available

Also reduce cron frequency to once a week which should be
enough (save a few watt-hours of energy)
